title: Verkhnenazarovskoye
text:
Verkhnenazarovskoye () is a <a href="types%20of%20inhabited%20localities%20in%20Russia">rural locality</a> (a <a href="Village%23Russia">selo</a>) in Sadovskoye Rural Settlement of <a href="Krasnogvardeysky%20District%2C%20Adygea">Krasnogvardeysky District</a>, <a href="Adygea">Adygea</a>, <a href="Russia">Russia</a>. The population was 581 as of 2018. There are 7 streets.
Geography.
Verkhnenazarovskoye is located 25 km southeast of <a href="Krasnogvardeyskoye%2C_Republic_of_Adygea">Krasnogvardeyskoye</a> (the district's administrative centre) by road. Sadovoye is the nearest rural locality.
Ethnicity.
The selo is inhabited by <a href="Kurds">Kurds</a> () and <a href="Russians">Russians</a> () according to the 2010 census.
